EPrints RAE Module - BRONZE RELEASE

FEATURES

- Enter measures of esteem (optionally on behalf of another user)
- Search for publications (optionally on behalf of another user)
- Add publications from search results to "selected" list (optionally on behalf of another user)
- View/export reports (Microsoft Word, Microsoft Excel)

MANUAL INSTALLATION

1. Create database tables

The following tables need to be added to the ARCHIVEID database:

CREATE TABLE `rae_data` (
  `userid` int(11) default NULL,
  `field` varchar(255) default NULL,
  `value` longtext,
  `chooserid` int(11) default NULL,
) ENGINE=MyISAM DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

CREATE TABLE `rae_selected` (
  `userid` int(11) NOT NULL default '0',
  `eprintid` int(11) NOT NULL default '0',
  `chooserid` int(11) default NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY  (`userid`,`eprintid`)
) ENGINE=MyISAM DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

2. Install scripts

Copy all files to /opt/eprints2/cgi/users/rae/.

Symlink the RAELoader.pm module to the /opt/eprints2/perl_lib/ directory.

3. Configuration

Copy the cfg/rae-phrases-en.xml and cfg/ArchiveRAEConfig.pm to the /opt/eprints2/archives/ARCHIVEID/cfg/ directory.

These configuration settings are based on those currently used by the University of Southampton Eprints repository and are provided as a starting point. You will need to adjust these settings to suit your EPrints setup.
